unittitle_ssm: Susan E. Wilson Collection on the American Peoples School
abstract_ssm: Susan E. Wilson's mother, Vivian Glenn Wilson, lived at the American Peoples School in the 1930s. The school, located at 67 Stevenson Place in the Bronx, was a progressive residential center for young men and women who work during the day and study in the evening. The Susan E. Wilson Collection on the American Peoples School (dated 1933-1937) consists of materials collected by Wilson's parents documenting the culture and politics of the American Peoples School in the Bronx. Materials include a blank membership application, ephemera, dance instructions, and a research paper. The collection also includes theater programs from the 1930s, many from the WPA Federal Theatre Project.
